snippet.textDisplay: My two biggest problems about the characters in the show is how they kind of skip their arks. Like Celadon goes from being imprisoned after being extremely badly treated by the skeksis to being good because her sister died. Based on her character development at that point, she should have been sad about Thavra and then be mad at her sister again for doing a rebellion and getiing Thavra killed. Then it really annoys me how Rian goes from losing what probably was the love of his life to trying to get with a girl he met two days ago in the span of like a week. I feel like he should have been given more time to mourn to show how the death affected his character, or even share his sadness with Deet to make their relationship grow stronger. But apart from that I absolutely love the show and I would recommend it to literally anyone.
snippet.textOriginal: My two biggest problems about the characters in the show is how they kind of skip their arks. Like Celadon goes from being imprisoned after being extremely badly treated by the skeksis to being good because her sister died. Then it really annoys me how Rian goes from losing what probably was the love of his life to trying to get with a girl he met two days ago in the span of like a week. I feel like he should have been given more time to mourn to show how the death affected his character, or even share his sadness with Deet to make their relationship grow stronger.
